TopicTitle: KSP WON'T START UP AFTER WILD BLUE INDUSTRIES MOD UPDATE

Articles.Content:
my ksp worked perfectly until mini-avc show me that i had to update all (wild blue industries) mods like:dsev

and heisenberg airships he ask me to update both blue industries mods but when i update them the ksp won't start up it will show a black screen for 1 seconds and then it stops and doesn't respond forever!!! mods:

*inter-installer extended

*near future solar

*near future launch vehicles

*near future construction

*near future spacecraft

*KIS 

*KAS

*TAC-LS

*modular grounded vehicles

*ground construction

*wild blue industries (all mods)

*extraplanetary launch pads

*kopernicus 

*environmental visual enchantments 

*scatterer

*hangar

*mech jeb

*kerbal engineer redux

there is no output log and i didn't install mods during the update of the others

notes:

when i click not responding ksp the windows play a sound and refuse to show the ksp window

also when i close normally the ksp  keeps running in the background as shown at task manager

after the ksp unlimited respond the ksp window get transparent showing my desktop and a small (old windows style) text window on top left says "kerbal space program"

We need the logs (both KSP.log and Player.log from Unity) in order to get an idea about what's happening.

But, on a wild guess, I think you just blew up some memory restriction. Try to delete some less used mods to see what happens.

and broke up again i discovered that when i run ksp via open gl the ksp brokes up !!!!! post:

[SNIP]

There must be something else killing your KSP. Something that must be changed at the same time you updated your WBI add-ons.
if you're using Steam, validate the integrity of game files.  That will check for any corruptions in the base game.

It says you are running KSP 1.4.3....your mods need to match the KSP version...whenever possible. ESPECIALLY for some of the mods you are running....

Are you using the regular KSP.exe or KSP_64.exe to launch the game? Or are you launching it through Steam or CKAN or something? I recommend just launching the shortcut yourself and not using a third party launcher to start the game....

You are running several VERY troublesome mods if they are not installed properly and for the correct version of the game. 

Extraplanetary Launchpads, Kopernicus, and I believe KIS/KAS, and most likely Interstellar (since it changes sooooo many things) have to be installed properly and for the correct version of KSP or they can totally break the game and even possibly your saves.

I have known EVE and scatterer to cause a memory leak if not installed correctly.

The visual enhancement mods are so tricky to install, I have seen a guide on the Internet on how to install them correctly.
